WEBVTT

01:40.380 --> 01:48.740
[You are My Fateful Love]
[EP07]

01:55.140 --> 01:56.500
What's that sound on your end?

01:57.660 --> 01:58.380
An ambulance siren.

02:00.819 --> 02:01.179
Why is there

02:01.179 --> 02:02.339
an ambulance?

02:03.100 --> 02:04.580
I'm at the hospital.

02:06.819 --> 02:08.059
Mr Xu, what happened?

02:09.020 --> 02:10.020
I have a stomachache.

02:10.819 --> 02:11.619
Nothing serious.

02:14.940 --> 02:15.940
Get some rest.

02:16.380 --> 02:17.259
Hope you feel better soon.

02:28.060 --> 02:28.940
What are you two doing here?

02:30.340 --> 02:32.139
You look a lot better.

02:32.699 --> 02:33.259
Does your stomach still hurt?

02:33.620 --> 02:34.220
No.

02:34.819 --> 02:35.859
No? Then eat something.

02:36.259 --> 02:36.819
There.

02:37.340 --> 02:37.900
Okay.

02:38.380 --> 02:38.859
I'm not hungry.

02:39.539 --> 02:40.660
You need to eat.

02:45.180 --> 02:46.620
Ambulance sirens?

02:47.259 --> 02:47.859
Mr Xu,

02:47.859 --> 02:49.180
why are you listening to that?

02:49.299 --> 02:49.699
Nothing.

02:49.699 --> 02:51.019
Just trying a new kind of music.

02:54.460 --> 02:55.299
That's rare.

02:56.660 --> 02:57.859
Never heard of

02:57.859 --> 02:59.460
anyone switching to

02:59.460 --> 03:00.859
ambulance sirens.

03:01.539 --> 03:02.660
What,

03:03.019 --> 03:04.419
life is too boring

03:04.500 --> 03:05.660
so you're looking for a thrill?

03:06.500 --> 03:07.100
Mr Xu,

03:07.180 --> 03:08.139
Ms Ruan is here

03:08.139 --> 03:08.940
to see you.

03:09.900 --> 03:11.100
Let her in, please. Thanks.

03:12.900 --> 03:14.060
How did Ruan Yu know you were hospitalized?

03:14.739 --> 03:15.819
Huaisong,

03:15.819 --> 03:17.220
you sly fox.

03:17.780 --> 03:19.299
I thought you were

03:19.299 --> 03:20.180
chasing thrills.

03:20.180 --> 03:21.579
Turns out you're chasing a girl.

03:22.819 --> 03:23.460
Take the thermos away.

03:23.979 --> 03:25.060
You can eat it yourself.

03:26.419 --> 03:27.419
I'm taking it now?

03:27.819 --> 03:28.259
Yeah.

03:48.780 --> 03:49.620
How could I

03:49.620 --> 03:51.019
know you skipped lunch?

03:51.019 --> 03:52.539
You didn't tell me.

03:53.180 --> 03:54.500
I didn't tell you?

03:54.699 --> 03:55.900
I sent you a WeChat message.

03:56.259 --> 03:57.259
You must've sent it to the wrong person.

03:57.259 --> 03:58.380
I never got anything.

04:14.139 --> 04:15.940
[Bring me some porridge at noon.]

04:22.460 --> 04:24.299
[Room 106, New District Hospital.]

04:30.859 --> 04:32.299
[So that message wasn't meant for me.]

04:32.979 --> 04:34.580
[Do I go in]

04:34.900 --> 04:35.820
[or not?]

04:37.179 --> 04:38.460
I want my porridge now.

04:40.580 --> 04:41.340
Fine.

04:41.340 --> 04:42.539
I'll go get some.

04:45.340 --> 04:46.059
Ms Ruan?

04:46.739 --> 04:47.340
Mr Liu,

04:48.260 --> 04:49.100
are you going to buy porridge?

04:49.739 --> 04:50.780
How did you know?

04:50.780 --> 04:51.780
Please, come in.

04:54.260 --> 04:55.020
Ms Ruan,

04:55.460 --> 04:56.260
what brings you here?

04:56.580 --> 04:57.220
Mr Xu,

04:57.900 --> 04:58.580
your porridge.

05:03.820 --> 05:04.619
That message was meant for Liu Mao.

05:04.619 --> 05:05.499
I sent it to you by mistake.

05:05.580 --> 05:06.379
I'm really sorry

05:06.499 --> 05:07.179
-  for the trouble.
- It's okay.

05:12.739 --> 05:13.419
Mr Xu,

05:13.660 --> 05:14.820
I didn't know you were sick.

05:14.979 --> 05:15.739
Otherwise,

05:16.059 --> 05:17.140
I never would've

05:17.140 --> 05:18.419
kept you on the case so late last night.

05:18.939 --> 05:19.460
It's fine.

05:20.900 --> 05:21.979
[At that time,]

05:21.979 --> 05:23.580
[he wasn't even admitted yet.]

05:24.140 --> 05:25.580
[On the way to the hospital,]

05:25.619 --> 05:26.780
[he kept staring]

05:26.780 --> 05:27.820
[at signal bars,]

05:28.100 --> 05:29.499
[afraid the call would drop.]

05:29.859 --> 05:31.260
[In case he woke others up,]

05:31.260 --> 05:32.900
[he didn't turn on his mic.]

05:33.660 --> 05:36.700
[Love does make one act like a fool.]

05:39.020 --> 05:39.580
Mr Xu,

05:40.179 --> 05:41.260
are you feeling better today?

05:41.700 --> 05:42.660
Not really.

05:43.580 --> 05:44.260
Huaisong,

05:44.660 --> 05:45.460
you need to

05:45.979 --> 05:48.419
take good care of your stomach.

05:48.739 --> 05:49.580
Do you know

05:49.780 --> 05:51.340
the stomach is sensitive to emotion?

05:51.619 --> 05:53.059
When you're in a good mood,

05:53.140 --> 05:53.820
the pain will be gone.

05:55.100 --> 05:55.739
Ms Ruan,

05:56.140 --> 05:56.900
you're a writer, right?

05:57.260 --> 05:58.460
You must be great with words.

05:58.700 --> 05:59.340
If you have time,

05:59.340 --> 06:01.020
come keep him company.

06:01.539 --> 06:02.780
Better mood,

06:03.059 --> 06:04.220
faster

06:04.739 --> 06:06.020
recovery.

06:07.379 --> 06:08.299
It's an old issue.

06:08.299 --> 06:09.059
Don't trouble her over it.

06:09.419 --> 06:10.820
How is that troubling her?

06:11.539 --> 06:12.059
Not at all.

06:12.539 --> 06:13.660
I'm already here,

06:13.820 --> 06:15.499
and I don't have other plans today.

06:16.939 --> 06:17.979
You heard that?

06:19.059 --> 06:20.260
She's so considerate.

06:22.260 --> 06:23.140
Alright. Thanks.

06:26.580 --> 06:27.820
Why are you eating it like that?

06:28.340 --> 06:29.900
That's how we do it in Su City.

06:30.379 --> 06:31.780
All locals eat porridge this way.

06:33.179 --> 06:34.979
How did you know

06:35.340 --> 06:36.580
I'm from Su City too?

06:39.140 --> 06:39.739
I looked into it.

06:45.539 --> 06:46.739
It's in your WeChat profile.

06:52.499 --> 06:53.299
Ms Ruan,

06:53.619 --> 06:54.660
you're here to see Mr Xu too?

06:56.739 --> 06:57.260
Mr Xu,

06:57.260 --> 06:58.499
didn't you just say you weren't...

06:58.499 --> 07:00.939
Alright, alright.

07:01.059 --> 07:01.660
Drop it.

07:02.939 --> 07:04.059
We should get going.

07:04.340 --> 07:05.260
Still got work back at the office.

07:05.820 --> 07:06.340
Gotta go.

07:07.739 --> 07:08.460
Oh right, Mr Xu,

07:08.619 --> 07:09.460
I just saw

07:09.460 --> 07:10.340
the email you

07:10.340 --> 07:11.260
sent at 3:00 AM.

07:11.260 --> 07:12.460
I'll send the files to you right away.

07:15.059 --> 07:15.900
[3:00 AM?]

07:16.260 --> 07:17.140
[Xu Huaisong said]

07:17.140 --> 07:18.020
[he fell asleep too,]

07:18.140 --> 07:19.499
[so he didn't hang up the call.]

07:21.419 --> 07:22.859
You mean I was sleepwalking

07:23.299 --> 07:23.979
at 3:00 AM?

07:27.939 --> 07:29.939
What he means is...

07:31.340 --> 07:32.340
You probably dreamed it.

07:33.660 --> 07:34.220
Yeah.

07:34.619 --> 07:35.820
I sent it to you, remember?

07:36.580 --> 07:37.419
- I sent it to him.
- Really?

07:37.419 --> 07:38.220
I sent it.

07:38.900 --> 07:39.379
Let's go.

07:41.660 --> 07:42.220
See you.

07:42.340 --> 07:43.020
Seriously?

07:44.419 --> 07:44.780
Have a seat.

07:48.340 --> 07:48.859
Wait, Mao,

07:48.859 --> 07:50.299
that email was definitely from Mr Xu.

07:52.460 --> 07:53.660
After all these years,

07:53.660 --> 07:54.499
you still can't

07:54.499 --> 07:55.539
read between the lines?

07:56.059 --> 07:56.780
Think about it.

08:09.260 --> 08:10.140
Come to think of it,

08:10.859 --> 08:12.260
Ms Ruan does act weird

08:12.260 --> 08:13.100
when Ms Ruan's around.

08:13.460 --> 08:14.739
Like the day he got back.

08:14.859 --> 08:15.979
He made me put on that act

08:15.979 --> 08:17.499
about Ms Zhang being in trouble.

08:18.299 --> 08:19.379
Then I called to ask

08:19.379 --> 08:20.179
when to pick him up

08:20.179 --> 08:21.580
but he said he hadn't eaten.

08:24.660 --> 08:26.020
He really is a sly fox.

08:39.539 --> 08:40.820
Mr Xu, you finished eating?

08:42.139 --> 08:42.659
Yeah.

08:43.379 --> 08:43.779
Okay.

08:44.300 --> 08:44.659
Thanks.

08:44.820 --> 08:45.220
It's nothing.

08:46.379 --> 08:47.220
Get some rest.

08:47.619 --> 08:48.540
I should head back.

08:49.060 --> 08:50.619
I've sorted out and brought along

08:50.619 --> 08:51.139
the plagiarism

08:51.139 --> 08:51.979
rebuttal files.

08:52.300 --> 08:53.499
Take a look when you got time.

08:54.340 --> 08:54.700
Okay.

08:54.859 --> 08:55.979
Can you hand them over?

09:00.580 --> 09:00.979
Here.

09:00.979 --> 09:01.820
Thanks.

09:11.779 --> 09:12.779
[She made you fried rice cakes]

09:12.779 --> 09:13.700
[and visited you in hospital.]

09:13.779 --> 09:15.139
[She's clearly got a thing for you.]

09:16.019 --> 09:17.859
[Why not make a move?]

09:18.220 --> 09:19.019
[You might have a shot.]

09:35.259 --> 09:35.859
Mr Xu,

09:36.180 --> 09:37.180
I'll get going then.

09:37.899 --> 09:38.300
Alright.

09:38.540 --> 09:39.779
Okay. Have some rest.

09:41.859 --> 09:42.340
Wait.

09:44.859 --> 09:45.899
There's always

09:46.420 --> 09:47.499
been a chapter missing

09:47.499 --> 09:48.379
from your document,

09:49.940 --> 09:51.259
Chapter 23.

10:15.139 --> 10:16.779
Huaisong?

10:32.619 --> 10:33.180
Yu,

10:35.220 --> 10:35.859
would

10:36.379 --> 10:37.220
you like...

10:47.019 --> 10:47.779
Can I

10:48.580 --> 10:49.499
take a look?

10:50.139 --> 10:50.619
No.

10:53.619 --> 10:54.460
Why?

10:55.100 --> 10:55.820
It's a

10:55.820 --> 10:57.340
transition chapter.

10:57.779 --> 10:58.820
It has to be important.

11:00.060 --> 11:00.619
It's...

11:01.820 --> 11:02.779
It's not that important.

11:03.100 --> 11:03.979
I'll decide

11:04.379 --> 11:05.700
after I read it.

11:07.820 --> 11:08.659
Right now?

11:09.259 --> 11:09.940
Right now.

11:10.899 --> 11:11.379
Have a seat.

11:22.580 --> 11:23.180
Mr Xu,

11:23.540 --> 11:24.540
I didn't bring the original file.

11:26.580 --> 11:28.859
It should be in the website backend, right?

11:29.739 --> 11:31.100
[How does a male lawyer]

11:31.460 --> 11:32.820
[know so well about the novel website]

11:32.820 --> 11:33.899
[for female readers?]

11:48.859 --> 11:49.540
Mr Xu,

11:49.859 --> 11:51.499
the signal in here is terrible.

11:51.739 --> 11:53.220
I'll send it to you when I get home.

11:53.940 --> 11:55.979
The hospital has Wi-Fi.

11:56.340 --> 11:57.700
Password is 66668888.

12:14.820 --> 12:15.899
I just sent it.

12:16.420 --> 12:17.460
I should get going.

12:25.220 --> 12:26.379
Mr Xu, what's wrong?

12:30.259 --> 12:31.659
Is your stomach acting up again?

12:31.659 --> 12:32.540
I'll go get a doctor.

12:32.540 --> 12:33.499
I'm fine, really.

12:36.379 --> 12:38.460
I've just been straining my eyes,

12:38.940 --> 12:39.379
and they hurt.

12:40.180 --> 12:41.139
[Wasn't he]

12:41.220 --> 12:42.979
[admitted for stomach pain?]

12:45.259 --> 12:46.379
My eyes are bothering me.

12:46.700 --> 12:47.540
Could you read the original for me?

12:47.659 --> 12:48.060
Thanks.

12:50.859 --> 12:51.700
What?

12:52.220 --> 12:53.540
I still remember the plot posted

12:53.540 --> 12:54.540
by The Poet online.

12:55.340 --> 12:56.139
Just read your original.

12:56.300 --> 12:57.540
If there are no overlaps,

12:57.540 --> 12:59.060
then we can wrap this up.

13:00.379 --> 13:01.619
[Sure, no problems for you.]

13:02.100 --> 13:03.899
[I'll be the one in big trouble.]

13:05.779 --> 13:06.859
No need, Mr Xu.

13:07.420 --> 13:08.180
I've already checked it.

13:08.180 --> 13:09.139
That chapter is clean.

13:10.220 --> 13:11.379
The most dangerous place

13:11.899 --> 13:13.340
is often the safest,

13:13.739 --> 13:14.580
and vice versa.

13:15.420 --> 13:16.940
The more convinced you are there's

13:17.619 --> 13:18.940
no problem, the more likely there is one.

13:21.739 --> 13:22.540
[It's fine, it's fine.]

13:23.060 --> 13:24.139
[It's the female lead's dream.]

13:24.460 --> 13:25.700
[Not mine.]

13:26.139 --> 13:27.259
[It's just]

13:27.460 --> 13:28.899
[a romantic scene.]

13:29.739 --> 13:31.379
[I can survive the embarrassment.]

13:58.619 --> 14:00.100
Chapter 23.

14:00.899 --> 14:01.820
He Shiqian...

14:02.379 --> 14:02.659
He...

14:02.659 --> 14:03.220
Never mind.

14:05.139 --> 14:06.499
I'll read it myself later.

14:08.540 --> 14:08.940
Okay.

14:11.659 --> 14:12.460
Mr Xu, I gotta go.

14:16.979 --> 14:17.460
Bye.

14:37.619 --> 14:38.180
[Huaisong,]

14:38.779 --> 14:39.940
[which ward are you in?]

14:40.259 --> 14:41.659
[Mom and I are coming to see you.]

14:46.940 --> 14:47.659
Mom, here we are.

14:49.180 --> 14:50.420
Stop eating so much candy.

14:50.820 --> 14:51.820
You're not a kid anymore.

14:52.259 --> 14:53.499
And start using floss.

14:59.700 --> 15:01.340
We came for a dentist appointment.

15:01.619 --> 15:02.499
Where are we?

15:04.019 --> 15:06.060
Mom, you're already here.

15:06.060 --> 15:07.340
Just go in and check on Huaisong.

15:07.340 --> 15:08.619
He's sick.

15:08.899 --> 15:09.379
This is exactly

15:09.379 --> 15:10.659
when he needs family around.

15:11.259 --> 15:12.220
I've told you

15:12.499 --> 15:13.499
I don't have a son.

15:14.019 --> 15:15.019
He is not my family.

15:15.700 --> 15:17.700
Oh, come on.

15:17.700 --> 15:20.019
Don't be upset. Don't talk like that.

15:20.420 --> 15:21.899
Go in by yourself if you want.

15:22.859 --> 15:23.979
You lied to me.

15:24.659 --> 15:25.659
Mom...

15:36.340 --> 15:36.940
Huaisong.

15:40.979 --> 15:42.019
Let me take a look at you.

15:42.259 --> 15:43.899
What happened?

15:45.139 --> 15:46.060
Are you okay?

15:46.499 --> 15:48.779
You look so pale,

15:48.859 --> 15:50.580
like you're on your deathbed.

15:50.859 --> 15:51.820
If you can't say anything nice,

15:51.820 --> 15:52.580
just shut up.

15:56.499 --> 15:57.420
Why did you come alone?

16:00.300 --> 16:02.580
Mom's really worried about you.

16:03.060 --> 16:03.899
She's just been

16:03.899 --> 16:04.899
swamped with work

16:05.259 --> 16:06.379
these past few days.

16:06.739 --> 16:08.700
So she asked me to come

16:08.700 --> 16:09.979
check on you.

16:14.139 --> 16:14.820
Mr Xu,

16:15.580 --> 16:16.540
I forgot something.

16:17.859 --> 16:18.340
Come in please.

16:19.859 --> 16:21.019
Who's that pretty lady?

16:21.300 --> 16:22.619
Not worried about me,

16:22.619 --> 16:24.180
but interested in a pretty lady?

16:25.499 --> 16:25.940
Sorry.

16:26.180 --> 16:26.619
Thanks.

16:26.619 --> 16:27.259
I'll head out now.

16:28.060 --> 16:28.619
Miss?

16:29.619 --> 16:31.220
Hi.

16:31.499 --> 16:32.460
I'm the little sister

16:32.580 --> 16:34.340
of this difficult but handsome guy.

16:34.340 --> 16:35.259
I'm Xu Huaishi.

16:36.060 --> 16:38.700
Hi, I'm Mr Xu's

16:40.460 --> 16:41.100
client.

16:41.540 --> 16:42.259
Client?

16:43.820 --> 16:45.100
Let me guess.

16:45.619 --> 16:47.300
You must be

16:47.300 --> 16:48.460
Ruan Yu, right?

16:52.259 --> 16:53.100
How did you know?

16:54.580 --> 16:57.220
Huaisong mentioned you before.

16:57.580 --> 16:59.619
He said he's been working on a case

16:59.619 --> 17:01.499
for a writer named Ruan Yu.

17:01.739 --> 17:02.859
You look like someone

17:02.859 --> 17:04.540
who's well-read

17:04.540 --> 17:05.859
and cultured.

17:05.859 --> 17:06.859
I figured it out right away.

17:08.340 --> 17:10.019
Can't believe Mr Xu has

17:10.019 --> 17:11.180
such a sweet and cute sister.

17:13.179 --> 17:14.780
Huaisong, you should

17:15.060 --> 17:16.419
reflect on why she's so surprised.

17:18.899 --> 17:19.980
I didn't mean it like that.

17:21.580 --> 17:22.459
It's fine.

17:22.820 --> 17:24.740
Everyone knows what he's like.

17:26.820 --> 17:27.419
If Mr Xu

17:27.419 --> 17:28.619
were half as sweet as you,

17:28.859 --> 17:29.740
he'd probably

17:29.740 --> 17:30.659
double his client list.

17:32.139 --> 17:33.340
Lawyers win cases

17:33.340 --> 17:34.300
through competence,

17:34.500 --> 17:35.500
not by being smooth talkers.

17:36.740 --> 17:38.899
I don't know

17:38.899 --> 17:39.859
if being sweet would

17:39.859 --> 17:40.820
get him more cases,

17:41.139 --> 17:43.580
but it would've kept him from being single.

17:46.859 --> 17:49.219
[Doesn't he have a girlfriend?]

17:50.020 --> 17:50.780
Well,

17:51.260 --> 17:52.980
even if pigs flew,

17:52.980 --> 17:54.540
he'd still remain single.

17:54.980 --> 17:55.659
He's been

17:55.659 --> 17:56.820
single for 28 years.

17:56.820 --> 17:58.100
I'd like to remind you

17:58.139 --> 17:59.540
spreading others' personal information

17:59.540 --> 18:00.540
could constitute a violation

18:00.540 --> 18:02.179
of personal data rights and defamation.

18:03.340 --> 18:05.820
I'm not spreading anything.

18:06.219 --> 18:08.020
Spreading is when you tell lots of people.

18:08.219 --> 18:09.060
I only

18:09.060 --> 18:10.939
told Yu about it.

18:11.100 --> 18:12.100
She won't tell

18:12.100 --> 18:13.939
anyone, right?

18:14.939 --> 18:15.659
Of course.

18:16.659 --> 18:18.179
Your secret is

18:18.260 --> 18:19.260
safe with me.

18:26.260 --> 18:27.219
Then go wash

18:27.219 --> 18:28.980
some fruit for this lady

18:28.980 --> 18:29.939
as hush money.

18:30.820 --> 18:31.699
On it.

18:32.659 --> 18:33.340
Please don't bother.

18:33.340 --> 18:34.379
I'm just here to grab my things.

18:34.540 --> 18:35.139
You're leaving?

18:35.139 --> 18:36.340
No trouble at all.

18:36.340 --> 18:37.580
I'm gonna have some fruit too.

18:39.540 --> 18:40.500
How about this? I...

18:40.500 --> 18:41.740
Let me wash the fruit instead.

18:41.899 --> 18:43.020
I need to wash this lunchbox anyway.

18:43.899 --> 18:45.219
You're too kind.

18:45.219 --> 18:45.580
It's fine, really.

18:45.580 --> 18:46.340
Let me help you.

18:46.340 --> 18:47.139
No need, no need.

18:50.659 --> 18:51.060
Close the door.

18:56.540 --> 18:58.219
What are you doing?

18:59.939 --> 19:00.780
When you're with her,

19:02.139 --> 19:03.179
don't say anything you shouldn't.

19:04.500 --> 19:05.219
Huaisong,

19:05.419 --> 19:07.859
I'm on your side.

19:08.340 --> 19:09.020
Think about it.

19:09.020 --> 19:10.100
With just a few sentences,

19:10.100 --> 19:11.659
I let her know you're still single.

19:11.980 --> 19:13.379
If she thought

19:13.379 --> 19:14.500
you had a girlfriend,

19:14.780 --> 19:15.980
even if she liked you,

19:15.980 --> 19:17.340
she wouldn't dare take a step forward.

19:17.699 --> 19:19.300
Stay out of grown-up business.

19:20.100 --> 19:20.899
If I don't step in,

19:20.899 --> 19:22.300
how much longer are you going to wait?

19:22.379 --> 19:23.659
Mr. Big Shot Lawyer,

19:24.179 --> 19:25.740
why are you and Yu

19:25.740 --> 19:26.899
still stuck as

19:26.899 --> 19:28.100
client and attorney?

19:28.100 --> 19:29.100
Have you ever thought about that?

19:29.219 --> 19:30.020
I know exactly why.

19:31.419 --> 19:32.100
Because

19:32.820 --> 19:34.300
she doesn't know I recognized her.

19:34.859 --> 19:35.899
Wrong.

19:36.219 --> 19:37.540
It's because you two

19:37.540 --> 19:39.340
haven't seen each other in years.

19:39.659 --> 19:40.340
You don't know

19:40.340 --> 19:41.820
if she still has feelings for you

19:42.179 --> 19:42.820
or if

19:43.340 --> 19:45.139
she'll fall for the real you.

19:45.260 --> 19:46.020
You're not sure,

19:46.020 --> 19:47.219
so you don't make a move.

19:47.260 --> 19:48.100
You're afraid you'll scare her off

19:48.100 --> 19:49.139
if you move too fast.

19:50.179 --> 19:50.859
Let's put it this way.

19:51.179 --> 19:52.580
Knowing how to win a case

19:52.580 --> 19:53.699
doesn't mean you know love.

19:53.939 --> 19:56.060
Knowing love doesn't mean you know women.

19:56.060 --> 19:56.939
You might understand women,

19:56.939 --> 19:58.340
but you don't know sin²x

19:58.340 --> 20:00.139
plus cos²x equals one.

20:00.619 --> 20:02.300
You're just being annoying.

20:02.899 --> 20:03.540
You're just

20:03.540 --> 20:04.659
a high schooler,

20:04.659 --> 20:05.340
yet here you are

20:05.340 --> 20:06.780
teaching a 28-year-old man how to date.

20:06.780 --> 20:08.020
You think that makes sense?

20:08.699 --> 20:10.139
You can underestimate your rivals,

20:10.139 --> 20:11.179
but never underestimate

20:11.179 --> 20:12.340
a Gen Z girl.

20:13.060 --> 20:13.780
I'm done talking to you.

20:13.820 --> 20:14.659
I'm going to

20:14.659 --> 20:15.659
bond with Yu.

20:16.580 --> 20:17.619
Don't say anything reckless.

20:20.459 --> 20:21.540
Let me help you.

20:22.619 --> 20:23.820
It's fine, I've got it.

20:23.939 --> 20:24.740
I insist.

20:25.820 --> 20:26.980
Let me stem the cherry tomatoes.

20:33.540 --> 20:34.179
Yu,

20:34.540 --> 20:36.219
Huaisong specifically

20:36.300 --> 20:38.179
told me to keep busy

20:38.300 --> 20:39.100
and talk less,

20:39.100 --> 20:39.820
or I'd annoy you.

20:40.300 --> 20:41.580
He's pretty considerate, right?

20:42.540 --> 20:44.659
He's a little too considerate.

20:45.379 --> 20:46.139
Honestly,

20:46.419 --> 20:47.740
I really enjoy talking to you.

20:48.859 --> 20:50.659
Who do you like talking to more,

20:50.659 --> 20:51.899
me or Huaisong?

20:54.619 --> 20:55.459
It's different.

20:55.780 --> 20:57.580
Talking to you makes me happy.

20:58.020 --> 21:00.820
Talking to him makes me feel at ease.

21:01.580 --> 21:03.540
He's incredibly professional

21:03.540 --> 21:04.219
when we discuss the case.

21:04.500 --> 21:05.659
What else

21:05.899 --> 21:07.379
do you think of him?

21:09.580 --> 21:10.260
What do I think?

21:11.659 --> 21:12.219
Well,

21:12.619 --> 21:14.419
writers like to create

21:14.419 --> 21:16.300
character archetypes.

21:16.500 --> 21:17.300
What kind of character

21:17.300 --> 21:18.379
would he be?

21:22.260 --> 21:24.340
If he were a character in a novel,

21:25.219 --> 21:26.580
he'd be

21:26.939 --> 21:27.939
the handsome, aloof,

21:27.939 --> 21:28.820
elite type.

21:31.100 --> 21:31.859
[Good news.]

21:32.340 --> 21:33.740
[His cold and aloof image is still intact.]

21:36.740 --> 21:37.419
Yu,

21:37.939 --> 21:38.619
you're so pretty.

21:38.619 --> 21:40.300
I bet lots of guys like you.

21:40.740 --> 21:41.740
Do you have a boyfriend?

21:46.219 --> 21:46.859
No.

21:47.939 --> 21:48.500
Then what kind

21:48.500 --> 21:49.659
of boys are you into?

21:50.419 --> 21:50.899
No, men.

21:54.179 --> 21:55.939
Sweet-talkers, just like you.

21:57.179 --> 21:57.820
[Crap.]

21:58.459 --> 21:59.500
[I played my part too well.]

21:59.820 --> 22:01.939
[But even without my help,]

22:01.939 --> 22:02.859
[Huaisong]

22:02.939 --> 22:04.980
[is sharp-tongued and never sweet.]

22:05.580 --> 22:07.580
[Is he already out of the game?]

22:10.659 --> 22:11.139
Huaishi,

22:11.580 --> 22:12.699
where did you come from?

22:13.179 --> 22:13.820
Su City.

22:14.300 --> 22:15.899
You're attending high school there?

22:16.340 --> 22:16.859
Yeah.

22:17.060 --> 22:18.379
I'm studying in Su City No. 1 High School,

22:18.619 --> 22:19.740
just like Huaisong did.

22:26.100 --> 22:26.780
Yu,

22:26.939 --> 22:28.699
how's that case you

22:28.899 --> 22:29.980
entrusted to him going?

22:32.340 --> 22:34.219
The hearing is coming up soon.

22:35.100 --> 22:36.699
Are you running into any trouble?

22:37.060 --> 22:37.899
We're missing

22:37.899 --> 22:39.179
one piece of evidence we'd planned on,

22:39.820 --> 22:40.740
but it shouldn't affect anything.

22:44.699 --> 22:45.619
[That must be]

22:45.619 --> 22:46.740
[the purchase agreement]

22:46.740 --> 22:48.060
[I was supposed to submit to the court.]

22:49.820 --> 22:51.179
[But the whole thing was made up.]

22:51.619 --> 22:52.580
[I can't fabricate]

22:52.580 --> 22:53.540
[transaction records.]

22:54.500 --> 22:56.820
[Submitting false evidence is illegal.]

23:03.939 --> 23:04.459
Yu,

23:04.939 --> 23:05.659
don't worry.

23:05.980 --> 23:07.459
If you need help, just go to Huaisong.

23:07.580 --> 23:08.219
He's the best.

23:14.020 --> 23:15.379
I'm back.

23:15.780 --> 23:17.260
Huaisong, have an apple.

23:18.179 --> 23:18.780
I'm good.

23:19.300 --> 23:19.939
Just give one

23:19.939 --> 23:20.699
to her.

23:21.219 --> 23:21.980
Yu, have one.

23:22.659 --> 23:23.060
Thanks.

23:23.899 --> 23:25.379
Can we add each other on WeChat?

23:25.899 --> 23:26.580
Huaishi.

23:27.060 --> 23:27.619
Sure.

23:28.300 --> 23:29.260
Show me your QR code.

23:30.939 --> 23:31.939
Let's keep in touch.

23:35.580 --> 23:36.179
Mr Xu,

23:36.540 --> 23:37.980
I won't disturb you any longer.

23:38.179 --> 23:38.980
Get some rest.

23:40.699 --> 23:41.899
Thanks for the apple.

23:42.780 --> 23:43.780
Thank you for the porridge.

23:45.580 --> 23:46.419
I'll head out.

23:46.740 --> 23:47.980
- Goodbye.
- Bye.

23:48.859 --> 23:49.540
Take care.

23:52.820 --> 23:53.419
Huaishi,

23:59.740 --> 24:00.859
what did you say to her out there?

24:01.780 --> 24:03.300
You don't even like apples.

24:06.060 --> 24:07.540
Big ones,

24:07.540 --> 24:08.580
small ones,

24:08.780 --> 24:10.419
red ones, or green ones,

24:10.740 --> 24:11.740
you don't like any of them.

24:12.100 --> 24:13.260
That's because what you really want

24:13.260 --> 24:14.260
isn't an apple.

24:14.859 --> 24:15.419
Stop talking in riddles.

24:16.659 --> 24:17.100
You don't get it.

24:17.740 --> 24:18.139
Huaisong,

24:19.060 --> 24:20.820
you've still got a lot to learn.

24:21.139 --> 24:22.580
It's fine. No rush.

24:22.780 --> 24:23.260
Take your time.

24:24.419 --> 24:25.980
I gotta go. Bye.

24:26.139 --> 24:27.859
Red apples and green apples?

24:27.859 --> 24:28.459
Bye.

24:38.060 --> 24:39.020
What's wrong with red apples?

25:33.020 --> 25:33.859
[Wrong.]

25:34.379 --> 25:35.699
It's because you two

25:35.699 --> 25:37.580
haven't seen each other in years.

25:37.820 --> 25:38.500
You don't know

25:38.500 --> 25:40.020
if she still has feelings for you

25:40.340 --> 25:41.020
or if

25:41.500 --> 25:43.260
she'll fall for the real you.

25:43.419 --> 25:44.179
You're not sure,

25:44.179 --> 25:45.379
so you don't make a move.

25:45.419 --> 25:46.260
You're afraid you'll scare her off

25:46.260 --> 25:47.300
if you move too fast.

25:58.260 --> 25:58.939
Hello, Huaisong?

26:00.540 --> 26:01.100
It's me.

26:01.300 --> 26:02.139
You're discharged?

26:02.820 --> 26:03.379
[Yes.]

26:04.580 --> 26:05.899
[I want to ask you something.]

26:07.540 --> 26:09.580
What were the red apples

26:09.699 --> 26:10.899
and green apples

26:10.899 --> 26:11.980
you mentioned earlier

26:13.020 --> 26:13.780
all about?

26:14.859 --> 26:15.740
Took you

26:15.740 --> 26:16.899
long enough.

26:17.740 --> 26:20.699
But it's not too late.

26:21.260 --> 26:22.459
Cut the crap.

26:23.139 --> 26:23.740
Get to the point.

26:24.820 --> 26:26.500
I asked Yu today

26:26.500 --> 26:28.020
what her type is.

26:30.659 --> 26:31.619
What did she say?

26:32.659 --> 26:34.179
She said...

26:35.020 --> 26:35.780
What?

26:36.540 --> 26:37.699
I'm a bit tired.

26:43.659 --> 26:45.979
She said she likes someone sweet-talking.

26:45.980 --> 26:47.820
She likes someone sweet-talking?

26:49.419 --> 26:50.260
But here's

26:50.260 --> 26:51.340
a friendly reminder.

26:51.899 --> 26:52.899
I don't think

26:52.899 --> 26:53.659
you should overdo

26:53.659 --> 26:54.659
the cold and aloof act.

26:55.619 --> 26:58.659
I think what she actually likes is...

26:59.659 --> 27:00.699
Is what?

27:01.619 --> 27:03.300
Is...

27:03.300 --> 27:04.300
What is it?

27:07.659 --> 27:08.179
I'm thirsty.

27:09.699 --> 27:10.179
Alright.

27:12.100 --> 27:12.659
Your water, please.

27:14.899 --> 27:16.379
Both cool and sweet-talking.

27:16.459 --> 27:18.260
Both cool and sweet-talking?

27:18.899 --> 27:19.580
Can someone

27:19.580 --> 27:21.740
actually be both?

27:24.139 --> 27:25.300
I know

27:25.300 --> 27:26.340
it's quite difficult.

27:28.300 --> 27:29.179
But

27:29.780 --> 27:30.859
I know someone

27:30.859 --> 27:31.699
who's a perfect example.

27:32.419 --> 27:33.139
Who?

27:37.139 --> 27:38.939
Huaishi's Romance Class is now in session.

27:39.139 --> 27:40.659
Guaranteed results, affordable fees.

27:40.659 --> 27:41.459
One-on-one coaching.

27:41.459 --> 27:42.580
Only 666 yuan.

27:48.540 --> 27:49.060
Transfer's done.

27:49.379 --> 27:50.619
Who is it? Tell me.

27:51.219 --> 27:52.780
You remember

27:52.899 --> 27:54.100
when I asked you for money

27:54.100 --> 27:54.939
to go to a concert?

27:55.100 --> 27:56.139
Yeah. And?

27:56.500 --> 27:57.340
Shican has

27:57.340 --> 27:58.139
this incredibly versatile

27:58.139 --> 27:59.699
stage presence.

28:00.379 --> 28:02.619
When he plays the guitar and sings ballads,

28:02.899 --> 28:04.540
he looks both elegant and aloof.

28:04.780 --> 28:05.419
Ballads?

28:05.619 --> 28:06.500
- That's right.
- Elegant.

28:06.780 --> 28:08.100
- Aloof.
- Exactly.

28:08.740 --> 28:09.379
Like this.

28:10.459 --> 28:10.939
Like this?

28:11.899 --> 28:12.859
No, like this.

28:14.580 --> 28:15.699
How are you so bad at this?

28:15.699 --> 28:17.179
Then what should it look like?

28:17.260 --> 28:18.659
- Like this.
- Like that?

28:18.939 --> 28:19.939
This is aloof?

28:19.939 --> 28:20.459
Correct.

28:21.980 --> 28:23.379
When he raps

28:23.540 --> 28:24.580
and dances,

28:25.219 --> 28:27.100
he looks fierce and cool.

28:27.740 --> 28:29.060
Fierce and cool?

28:29.219 --> 28:30.980
Fierce. Cool.

28:31.699 --> 28:33.300
- Fierce.
- Cool.

28:34.419 --> 28:35.100
No.

28:35.540 --> 28:36.060
No?

28:36.619 --> 28:37.300
Fierce.

28:37.580 --> 28:38.300
Fierce.

28:38.580 --> 28:39.219
Cool.

28:39.459 --> 28:40.139
Cool.

28:42.820 --> 28:43.459
Like this?

28:44.939 --> 28:45.899
Yes, yes.

28:45.899 --> 28:47.139
- And this?
- Exactly.

28:47.139 --> 28:49.020
Just like that.

28:49.379 --> 28:51.060
You're a natural.

28:51.139 --> 28:51.939
- It's nothing.
- Besides,

28:52.020 --> 28:53.820
And when he meets fans,

28:54.100 --> 28:55.260
he's incredibly kind

28:55.260 --> 28:56.619
and sweet.

29:00.699 --> 29:03.699
You're so charming!

29:04.020 --> 29:05.219
What should I say to sound cool?

29:05.780 --> 29:06.779
Say something sweet.

29:06.780 --> 29:07.580
Sweet?

29:08.260 --> 29:09.699
Something sweet?

29:10.740 --> 29:11.939
Your hair looks great.

29:12.260 --> 29:14.740
You're so hot!

29:14.740 --> 29:16.300
Good job.

29:16.820 --> 29:17.459
Now

29:17.820 --> 29:18.899
you can look up

29:18.980 --> 29:19.899
his videos online

29:19.980 --> 29:21.260
and really study him.

29:22.540 --> 29:23.740
So who exactly

29:23.740 --> 29:25.379
have you been talking about?

29:27.340 --> 29:28.659
I forgot to introduce him.

29:28.899 --> 29:30.939
His name is Li Shican.

29:34.419 --> 29:35.580
Li Shican?

29:39.219 --> 29:40.619
So let me get this straight.

29:40.780 --> 29:41.899
The money I gave you

29:41.899 --> 29:44.060
was spent on this guy?

29:45.300 --> 29:47.020
And now you want me to copy him

29:47.540 --> 29:49.179
to win over Ruan Yu?

29:49.580 --> 29:50.260
That's right.

29:51.100 --> 29:52.060
And while you're at it,

29:52.060 --> 29:53.699
remember the Rule of Six Hearts,

29:54.459 --> 29:55.459
a caring heart,

29:55.459 --> 29:56.459
a patient heart, a loyal heart,

29:56.659 --> 29:57.659
a sincere heart,

29:57.659 --> 29:58.859
a devoted heart,

29:59.020 --> 30:00.419
so she can see your true heart.

30:00.820 --> 30:02.939
You have absolutely no heart.

30:03.260 --> 30:03.899
Check your phone.

30:09.659 --> 30:10.859
Why did you cancel the transfer?

30:10.859 --> 30:12.340
Not just the transfer.

30:12.340 --> 30:13.419
Your allowance for next month

30:13.419 --> 30:14.740
and the month after

30:14.740 --> 30:15.820
is gone too.

30:21.340 --> 30:21.939
Wait, you...

30:25.219 --> 30:25.980
It's ridiculous.

30:37.100 --> 30:38.540
[Stop the gossip.]

30:38.980 --> 30:39.580
[The fact]

30:39.580 --> 30:40.659
[that Lily Vale wrote this story]

30:40.859 --> 30:41.699
[means she's totally]

30:41.699 --> 30:42.500
[over that guy]

30:42.500 --> 30:43.500
[from her past.]

30:44.020 --> 30:45.459
[Why else would she name]

30:45.459 --> 30:47.060
[the male lead He Shiqian?]

30:47.500 --> 30:48.300
[The name means]

30:48.300 --> 30:50.580
[celebrating the passing of time.]

31:03.619 --> 31:04.899
[One will learn to move on eventually.]

31:06.060 --> 31:07.300
[It's just that there's no going back.]

31:26.139 --> 31:26.659
Hello?

31:28.179 --> 31:29.060
Wanna grab a drink?

31:47.500 --> 31:48.459
Are you trying to

31:48.459 --> 31:49.580
kill yourself?

31:51.340 --> 31:52.699
You were just hospitalized yesterday

31:52.980 --> 31:53.859
for stomachache.

31:56.020 --> 31:57.300
[One will learn to move on eventually.]

31:58.500 --> 31:59.659
[It's just that there's no going back.]

32:02.699 --> 32:03.179
Hello?

32:04.139 --> 32:06.780
Did the alcohol get your tongue?

32:09.219 --> 32:10.379
You've been

32:10.379 --> 32:12.540
drinking in silence since I got here.

32:14.459 --> 32:15.219
Do you know what time it is?

32:15.820 --> 32:16.699
I keep regular hours

32:16.699 --> 32:17.939
and take care of my health.

32:17.939 --> 32:20.060
I'm already feeling sleepy.

32:25.340 --> 32:26.500
If you won't talk, I'm out of here.

32:31.100 --> 32:32.139
Stop drinking.

32:33.020 --> 32:33.980
Say something or I'm leaving.

32:35.340 --> 32:36.219
Talk about what?

32:38.459 --> 32:39.699
Your blind date?

32:45.699 --> 32:46.659
Oh come on,

32:46.740 --> 32:47.780
that's what this is about?

32:48.740 --> 32:49.899
How many times do I have to tell you

32:49.899 --> 32:51.459
that blind date was over

32:51.459 --> 32:52.980
before it started?

32:53.340 --> 32:54.100
In less than five minutes,

32:54.100 --> 32:55.459
she became my client.

32:57.619 --> 32:58.379
And you

32:58.379 --> 32:59.060
fried rice cakes

32:59.060 --> 32:59.699
with her

32:59.699 --> 33:00.459
and made video calls

33:00.459 --> 33:01.619
across time zones.

33:01.619 --> 33:02.500
How could you

33:02.500 --> 33:03.060
never say

33:03.060 --> 33:03.820
a word to me?

33:06.340 --> 33:07.340
What's the point of that?

33:08.580 --> 33:09.619
If you don't tell me anything,

33:09.619 --> 33:11.459
how am I supposed to help you

33:11.459 --> 33:14.060
figure out if there's still a chance?

33:16.899 --> 33:17.619
What's standing

33:17.619 --> 33:18.699
between you two?

33:18.699 --> 33:19.859
Just spit it out.

33:19.859 --> 33:21.500
You're killing me here!

33:28.820 --> 33:29.859
If I told you,

33:30.780 --> 33:31.939
your jaw would hit the floor.

33:35.580 --> 33:36.459
Try me.

33:36.580 --> 33:37.580
What kind of

33:37.740 --> 33:39.619
jaw-dropping story could

33:40.060 --> 33:41.179
possibly shock

33:41.179 --> 33:42.419
a thirty-year-old man?

33:56.780 --> 33:57.619
In that case,

33:57.619 --> 33:59.179
you fell for her

33:59.179 --> 34:00.619
before you even got a good look

34:00.820 --> 34:01.540
at her face.

34:04.980 --> 34:05.419
Why...

34:06.219 --> 34:07.139
Why didn't you just

34:07.139 --> 34:08.820
tell her you liked her back then?

34:12.300 --> 34:13.780
You know what my family was

34:14.540 --> 34:15.580
going through at that time.

34:23.940 --> 34:25.139
Get out of this building.

34:25.259 --> 34:27.020
Your family are a bunch of

34:27.020 --> 34:27.940
parasites.

34:28.179 --> 34:28.940
What did you just call me?

34:29.299 --> 34:30.860
I'm talking to you,

34:31.219 --> 34:32.739
accomplice to a murderer.

34:36.420 --> 34:37.980
So what's your plan now?

34:42.219 --> 34:42.819
I don't know.

34:51.060 --> 34:52.659
I'm not afraid she never liked me.

34:54.699 --> 34:55.860
I'm afraid she did.

34:58.259 --> 34:58.860
I get it.

35:00.460 --> 35:01.420
Unrequited love isn't the worst part.

35:01.900 --> 35:02.900
The worst part is

35:04.259 --> 35:05.179
finding out years later

35:05.179 --> 35:06.179
that you two

35:07.299 --> 35:07.900
could've

35:07.900 --> 35:09.060
been together.

35:13.100 --> 35:14.699
The male lead

35:16.219 --> 35:17.460
in her novel is named

35:18.540 --> 35:19.619
He Shiqian.

35:22.580 --> 35:23.100
He

35:24.500 --> 35:25.420
means "to celebrate".

35:26.860 --> 35:27.739
Shiqian means

35:28.739 --> 35:29.980
"as time passes, things change."

35:32.500 --> 35:33.380
So the name

35:33.619 --> 35:35.460
means celebrating the passing of time.

35:40.819 --> 35:41.420
Dude,

35:41.779 --> 35:43.020
this is real life,

35:44.420 --> 35:45.420
not some TV show.

35:46.179 --> 35:48.060
You can't just write

35:48.500 --> 35:50.259
"ten years later"

35:50.580 --> 35:51.420
on a line

35:51.580 --> 35:52.900
and move on like

35:52.900 --> 35:53.860
nothing ever happened.

35:54.659 --> 35:55.339
I don't think

35:55.339 --> 35:56.500
Ruan Yu has zero

35:56.500 --> 35:57.659
feelings for you.

36:01.179 --> 36:03.020
But have you heard of something called

36:04.819 --> 36:05.779
a phantom crush?

36:07.100 --> 36:08.380
What is it?

36:11.219 --> 36:12.299
Let me tell you a story.

36:17.699 --> 36:18.380
I have a friend

36:19.139 --> 36:20.460
who fell for

36:20.779 --> 36:21.860
a girl right at

36:21.940 --> 36:22.819
the start

36:22.860 --> 36:24.139
of college.

36:26.139 --> 36:27.139
But neither of them ever

36:27.139 --> 36:28.139
made a move.

36:28.380 --> 36:29.819
Right before graduation,

36:29.819 --> 36:30.739
someone told him

36:31.100 --> 36:33.020
that she'd liked him all along.

36:35.060 --> 36:35.619
And then?

36:35.739 --> 36:36.980
He went all in

36:36.980 --> 36:38.460
and chased her.

36:39.299 --> 36:40.139
Then they got together.

36:40.980 --> 36:42.100
But once they were together,

36:42.739 --> 36:44.580
he realized something was off.

36:45.380 --> 36:46.259
They didn't

36:46.739 --> 36:48.339
know each other at all.

36:49.299 --> 36:49.860
All that time

36:49.860 --> 36:51.739
they'd been in love,

36:52.420 --> 36:53.940
they were just

36:53.940 --> 36:56.380
in love with the idea

36:56.380 --> 36:57.860
of each other.

36:59.980 --> 37:01.100
That's a phantom crush.

37:04.139 --> 37:05.699
He told me later

37:05.900 --> 37:06.659
when he was

37:07.219 --> 37:08.179
chasing her

37:08.179 --> 37:09.299
like crazy,

37:09.299 --> 37:11.139
he was actually

37:11.139 --> 37:13.060
driven by the fear

37:13.060 --> 37:15.020
of regret and

37:15.619 --> 37:16.460
obsession.

37:17.619 --> 37:18.139
He thought

37:18.139 --> 37:19.299
if he didn't go for it,

37:19.299 --> 37:20.699
he'd miss the chance.

37:21.739 --> 37:23.380
After he cooled down and they broke up,

37:23.739 --> 37:24.460
he regretted it.

37:24.580 --> 37:26.060
He wasn't being rational.

37:27.219 --> 37:28.100
They could have

37:28.100 --> 37:29.380
stayed perfect in

37:29.380 --> 37:30.860
each other's memories.

37:32.739 --> 37:33.900
But he shattered all of that

37:34.460 --> 37:35.540
the moment he

37:36.060 --> 37:36.900
acted on impulse.

37:38.139 --> 37:39.619
So I'm just trying to say

37:40.060 --> 37:41.179
sometimes

37:41.179 --> 37:43.100
having regrets isn't a bad thing.

37:43.580 --> 37:44.500
Chasing it might

37:44.900 --> 37:46.500
give you a different kind of regret,

37:47.139 --> 37:47.619
right?

37:48.580 --> 37:51.060
Think it through

37:51.540 --> 37:52.259
before you act.

38:04.779 --> 38:05.299
Right. Act.

38:10.940 --> 38:11.540
Act?

38:13.739 --> 38:14.339
I said all that,

38:14.339 --> 38:15.380
and you just heard one word

38:15.380 --> 38:16.060
'act'?

38:26.179 --> 38:26.619
Hello?

38:26.980 --> 38:27.380
Hello?

38:27.699 --> 38:28.500
Where are you going?

38:29.100 --> 38:29.619
I'm in a cab.

38:30.179 --> 38:31.060
Back to your apartment?

38:32.100 --> 38:32.659
To her place.

38:34.940 --> 38:36.060
To Ruan Yu's place?

38:36.860 --> 38:37.139
What are you doing?

38:37.139 --> 38:38.339
I just told you

38:38.339 --> 38:39.500
to stay calm.

38:39.500 --> 38:40.139
What's gotten into you?

38:40.179 --> 38:41.540
Are you going to confess?

38:46.060 --> 38:46.659
He hung up on me?

38:54.779 --> 38:55.619
[In that case,]

38:55.619 --> 38:57.179
[you fell for her before you]

38:57.179 --> 38:58.659
[even got a good look]

38:58.819 --> 38:59.659
[at her face.]

39:09.299 --> 39:09.819
Sir,

39:09.980 --> 39:10.980
has the Galactic Empire

39:10.980 --> 39:11.619
comic come in yet?

39:12.259 --> 39:13.779
Sorry, you missed it.

39:14.500 --> 39:15.580
Someone just borrowed the only copy.

39:17.179 --> 39:18.299
The good-looking guy over there.

39:19.940 --> 39:20.980
Judging by the uniform,

39:21.179 --> 39:22.500
he's from your school.

39:23.940 --> 39:25.819
Why don't you go talk to him?

39:28.819 --> 39:30.100
Looks like he's asleep, though.

39:34.819 --> 39:35.739
Never mind.

39:36.659 --> 39:37.779
I'll wait till he finishes

39:37.980 --> 39:38.659
and borrow it after.

39:39.139 --> 39:39.619
Alright.

39:45.100 --> 39:47.020
There's nothing better than

39:47.860 --> 39:48.659
dozing off over

39:48.659 --> 39:50.259
your favorite comic on a sunny

39:50.980 --> 39:52.060
weekend afternoon.

39:53.179 --> 39:54.060
Life

39:54.420 --> 39:55.819
should be full of

39:56.100 --> 39:57.460
happy moments like this.

39:57.460 --> 39:57.900
Exactly.

40:02.100 --> 40:03.100
[Do you have any idea]

40:03.100 --> 40:04.500
[how much pressure]

40:05.219 --> 40:06.779
[I'm under now?]

40:06.940 --> 40:07.779
[No, I don't.]

40:08.380 --> 40:09.219
[Why did you have to]

40:09.619 --> 40:11.299
[throw away our perfectly]

40:11.860 --> 40:12.779
[good life?]

40:12.940 --> 40:13.779
[Why did you have to]

40:13.779 --> 40:14.819
[take this case?]

40:16.060 --> 40:17.299
[It's my job.]

40:17.779 --> 40:18.779
[I'm a lawyer.]

40:19.540 --> 40:20.100
You're not

40:20.100 --> 40:21.339
the only lawyer in this city.

40:22.380 --> 40:23.500
Everyone else turned it down.

40:23.500 --> 40:24.380
Why did it have to be you?

40:25.619 --> 40:27.299
[Can't you just try to understand me?]

40:27.659 --> 40:28.540
[You dare say]

40:28.540 --> 40:29.219
[I don't understand you?]

40:29.219 --> 40:30.540
[After all these years?]

40:31.219 --> 40:32.659
[Have you thought about the kids?]

40:32.659 --> 40:33.900
[Have you thought about us?]

40:34.380 --> 40:35.500
[You're being unreasonable.]

41:09.179 --> 41:10.699
[What if every memory of joy]

41:11.139 --> 41:12.779
[is swallowed by grief?]

41:14.179 --> 41:15.299
[I must search.]

41:15.819 --> 41:17.580
[Even if the endless powdering of stars]

41:17.580 --> 41:19.259
[in the Galaxy makes the quest seem hopeless,]

41:20.020 --> 41:21.699
[and even if I must do it alone.]

41:22.179 --> 41:23.299
[This line from Galactic Empire]

41:23.299 --> 41:23.980
[is for you,]

41:24.219 --> 41:25.739
[a stranger who read the same comic as me.]

41:26.500 --> 41:27.299
[Life]

41:27.619 --> 41:28.460
[can be bright]

41:28.460 --> 41:29.540
[and carefree,]

41:29.940 --> 41:31.139
[or it can drag you down]

41:31.139 --> 41:32.219
[and leave you lost.]

41:32.779 --> 41:33.819
[Should the bitterness consume you,]

41:34.299 --> 41:35.380
[keep seeking]

41:35.580 --> 41:37.619
[and creating moments of joy.]

42:25.739 --> 42:26.259
Come on.

42:27.580 --> 42:29.779
Xu Huaisong, you've got this.

42:31.540 --> 42:32.219
You can do it.

43:05.500 --> 43:07.179
Don't touch it. You'll cut yourself.

43:10.460 --> 43:11.259
It's fine.

43:11.259 --> 43:12.380
I'll clean it up later.

43:23.580 --> 43:24.179
Well,

43:24.299 --> 43:25.100
Mr Xu, just leave it.

43:25.100 --> 43:25.860
I'll take care of it.

43:26.299 --> 43:27.779
A cloth and some tape.

43:29.179 --> 43:29.659
Got it.

43:39.020 --> 43:39.819
Mr Xu.

44:06.420 --> 44:07.460
This type of bowl

44:07.779 --> 44:09.219
doesn't break into shards, right?

44:10.699 --> 44:11.460
What if it does?

44:31.659 --> 44:32.420
It's done.

44:33.779 --> 44:34.460
Mr Xu,

44:34.739 --> 44:36.540
go wash your hands and eat.

44:38.219 --> 44:38.659
Okay.

44:41.179 --> 44:42.460
Mr Xu, give it to me.

44:42.619 --> 44:44.179
No need. There are shards on it.

44:47.219 --> 44:47.819
That way.
